[thinking] **Considering method coverage**
[thinking] 
[thinking] If a subclass calls an inherited method, the coverage call site remains attributed to the active class, which is interesting. However, the reporting class might display the call site in a way that suggests it's covered by a subclass, even though it's linked to the original class. There’s definitely a one-to-one connection here, and it seems important to keep this in mind when analyzing coverage reports. I should be aware of these distinctions!
